### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe the problem.

#### Motivation
Some password policies require â€˜a password must contains at least two or three of the followings: upper case letters, lower case letters, digits, non-alphanumeric characters'.

This scenario is not covered by current PasswordValidator implementation.

#### Example
Assum we have policy:
> A password must contains at least two of the followings:
> - upper case letters
> - lower case letters
> - digits
> - non-alphanumeric characters.

|Sample Password| Character kinds contained | Character kinds not contained |
|:---|:---|:---|
|`ABC123`| 2 (Upper case letters and digits)| 2 (Lower case letters and non-alphanumeric letters) |
|`abc###`| 2 (Lower case letters and non-alphanumeric letters)| 2 (Upper case letters and digits) |
|`abcabc`| 1 (Lower case letters)| 3 (Upper case letters and digits and non-alphanumeric letters) |

With current PasswordValidator, there's no combination of configuration that line 1 and line 2 will pass the validation and line 3 will fail the validation.

### Describe the solution you'd like

#### Add a new configuration option in `PasswordOptions`
``` csharp
public class PasswordOptions
{
    /* Original code omitted */

    /// <summary>
    /// Gets or sets the minimum number of character types which a password must contain. Defaults to 0.
    /// </summary>
    public int RequiredCharTypes { get; set; } = 0;
}
```

#### Add a new enum in `PasswordValidator.cs`
``` csharp
file enum CharTypes
{
    Other = 0,
    Digit = 1,
    Lower = 2,
    Upper = 3,
}
```

#### Add a new method in `PasswordValidator.cs`
``` csharp
private int[] CalculatePassword(string? password)
{
    int[] charTypes = new int[4];
    foreach (char c in password!)
    {
        if (IsDigit(c))
        {
            charTypes[(int)CharTypes.Digit] = 1;
        }
        else if (IsLower(c))
        {
            charTypes[(int)CharTypes.Lower] = 1;

        }
        else if (IsUpper(c))
        {
            charTypes[(int)CharTypes.Upper] = 1;
        }
        else
        {
            charTypes[(int)CharTypes.Other] = 1;
        }
    }
    return charTypes;
}
```

#### Change `ValidateAsync` method in `PasswordValidator.cs`
``` csharp
